text: when the FED wants to fight inflation it
raises interest rates which sets off a
chain reaction in the economy we built
this machine to show you how it
works it all starts when the FED makes
money more expensive for big Banks and
hedge funds and that pushes up shortterm
and long-term
rates now more people want the dollar
making it stronger and stronger and more
people want bonds so stock prices fall
so while you might earn more with your
savings account you'll pay more on your
credit cards and Loans this might make
you buy
less which means businesses could sell
less hire fewer workers and put things
on sale all slowing the economy and if
everything goes as expected inflation
will fall
but it's a delicate system and there are
a lot of places where the machine could
fail so like many of us the FED will be
watching the economy to see what happens
next
[Music]
